    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Embedded air pockets used as decoration of glass, comprising large, intentionally created air bubbles or tears, arranged in a decorative pattern, often in criss-crossed diagonal rows or spirals. Often seen in the stems of 18th-century and later wine glasses, particularly English.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000021271/Newman, Illustrated Dictionary of Glass (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000011151/Fleming and Honour, Penguin Dictionary of the Decorative Arts (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Decoración de vidrio en forma de bolsillos de aire incrustados, más grandes que las burbujas de aire o lágrimas comunes, colocadas en un modelo decorativo, a menudo en filas diagonales entrecruzadas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Glasdecoratie in de vorm van ingekapselde met lucht gevulde holten, groter dan gewone luchtbelletjes of tranen, gerangschikt in een decoratief patroon, vaak als kriskras aangebrachte rijen diagonalen of spiralen. Vaak aangetroffen in de steel van wijnglazen uit de 18de eeuw en later, met name bij Engelse wijnglazen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>比一般的氣泡或淚珠大型的嵌入式氣泡狀玻璃裝飾，通常是呈十字形交叉的斜紋或螺旋紋，以裝飾形式組成；常在十八世紀的高腳酒杯與之後的酒杯上見到，特別是英格蘭酒杯。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
